needGwtEvent

public boolean needGwtEvent()
                     throws ResultException
A GwtEvent is only required if the event is destined for the EventBus i.e. if anyone is firing or handling the event. If an event is only used locally, we don't bother generating the GwtEvent.

A special case exists for events that are defined in base modules but never fired in that module. In that case the firedInThisModule flag is set to false and, in that case, we will always generate the event.

Returns:
true the event is fired or handled by any component.
Throws:
ResultException - if the event is handled but never fired.
